==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: First-rate
<hw>First"-rate`</hw> <pr>(f⟦etil⟧rst"r⟦amac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Of the highest excellence; pre⟦eum⟧minent in quality, size, or
estimation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our only <qex>first-rate</qex> body of contemporary poetry is the
German.</q> <rj><qau>M. Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hermocrates . . . a man of <qex>first-rate</qex> ability.</q>
<rj><qau>Jowett (Thucyd).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>First-rate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: First-rate
<hw>First"-rate`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A war
vessel of the highest grade or the most powerful class.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>first-rate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: first-rate
